dc_title_s: The state of Florida compiled in the Bureau of Topographical Engineers, from the best authorities; by J. Goldsborough Bruff; D. McClelland, sc., 1846.
dc_description_s: Relief shown by hachures. Insets: Key West -- Mouths of the Suwanee River and the Cedar Keys -- General map of part of Florida included between Cedar Keys and St. John's River. Map indicates townships. 1 map; 105 x 101 cm This map is in the public domain. Please attribute access and use of this digitized map to the Stephen S. Clark Library, University of Michigan Library.
